com.hpe.caf.worker.document.model

Interface Script

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DocumentWorkerObject

    public interface Script
extends DocumentWorkerObject
    Represents a customization script which is attached to a task.

    The customization script may or may not be loaded. If it is loaded then any event handlers that it contains will be executed when the event occurs. The customization script can only be modified when it is not loaded.

    The customization script may or may not be installed. If it is installed then it will be included in the response message. If the response message is sent to another Document Worker then it will automatically be loaded by that worker before the task is processed.

      • getName

        String getName()
        Returns the name of the customization script.

        This can be used as an identifier for the script. It may appear in the log file, especially if there is an issue with the script.

        Returns:
        the name of the customization script

      • getObject

        Object getObject()
        This property allows for communication between scripts. When the customization script is loaded it may define a global variable named "thisScriptObject". This property can be used to access the contents of that global variable, which could be an object of any type, including a function. If the script is not loaded, or if the global variable is not set by the script, then null is returned.
        Returns:
        an object that the script has elected to expose, or null if the script is not loaded or does not expose an object

      • getScript

        String getScript()
          throws IOException
        Retrieves the text of the script.

        Note that there is no guarantee that the script code is cached. If the script is remote then calling this method multiple times may result in it being fetched multiple times.

        Returns:
        the source code of the script
        Throws:
        IOException - if the script is remote and cannot be retrieved

      • install

        void install()
        Installs this customization script. Calling this method has no effect if the script is already installed.

        Installing this script means that it will be included in the response message.

      • isInstalled

        boolean isInstalled()
        Checks whether this customization script is currently installed.

        If it is installed then it will be included in the response message, otherwise it will not be.

        Returns:
        true if this customization script is installed

      • isLoaded

        boolean isLoaded()
        Checks whether this customization script is currently loaded.

        The customization script must be loaded in order for its event handlers to be fired. It can only be modified when it is not loaded.

        Returns:
        true if this customization script is loaded

      • load

        void load()
   throws ScriptException
        Loads this customization script. Calling this method has no effect if the script is already loaded.
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if the script has not been initialized
        ScriptException - if the script cannot be retrieved or interpreted, or if it throws an error when loading

      • setName

        void setName(String name)
        Sets the name of the customization script. This may be used as an identifier for the script. If there is an issue with the script then it may appear in log files or in error messages.

        This method will throw a RuntimeException if it is called when the script is currently loaded.

        Parameters:
        name - the name of the customization script
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if this customization script is currently loaded

      • setScriptByReference

        void setScriptByReference(String reference)
        Sets the customization script. This method may be used when the script has been stored in the remote data store using the UTF-8 encoding. It does not verify that the remote data store reference is valid. No attempt will be made to download the script from the remote data store until the script is loaded.

        This method will throw a RuntimeException if it is called when the script is currently loaded.

        Parameters:
        reference - the reference to the script in the remote data store
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if this customization script is currently loaded

      • setScriptByUrl

        void setScriptByUrl(URL url)
        Sets the customization script. This method may be used when the location of the script is identified by the specified URL. If the script does not contain a recognized Unicode BOM then it is assumed to be UTF-8 encoded. No attempt will be made to download the script until it is loaded.

        This method will throw a RuntimeException if it is called when the script is currently loaded.

        Parameters:
        url - the reference to the location where the script can be retrieved from
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if this customization script is currently loaded, or if the specified URL is not strictly formatted in accordance with RFC2396

      • setScriptInline

        void setScriptInline(String script)
        Sets the customization script. This method may be used to directly specify a customization script so that it does not need to be downloaded from an external location in order to be loaded.

        This method will throw a RuntimeException if it is called when the script is currently loaded.

        Parameters:
        script - the customization script
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if this customization script is currently loaded

      • uninstall

        void uninstall()
        Uninstalls this customization script. Calling this method has no effect if the script is already uninstalled.

        Uninstalling this script means that it will not be included in the response message.

      • unload

        void unload()
        Unloads this customization script. Calling this method has no effect if the script is already unloaded.

        Unloading this script means that its event handlers will no longer be fired. It is required that the script is first unloaded in order to make any modifications to it.
